svc — query and control system services

SYNOPSIS
  svc list
  svc status ID
  svc start ID
  svc stop ID

DESCRIPTION
  Inspects and controls services managed by /sys/svc/init. Services
  are declared by unit files in /etc/services/<id>.cfg and supervised
  with restart-on-failure semantics.

  list      summarises every loaded service
  status    prints the unit + runtime fields for ID
  start     starts ID (and any unsatisfied dependencies)
  stop      asks ID to exit cooperatively (5 s grace)

EXAMPLES
  svc list
  svc start uid                  start the GUI session

CONFLICTS
  Some services declare conflicts={} in their unit and the manager
  will stop the named peers before starting. Sessiond and uid use a
  finer ipc-level pause/resume rather than conflicts because they
  share the same screen.

SEE ALSO
  ps(1), kill(1), services(5)
